  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>The primary endpoint is the incidence at 12 months on the originally implanted device of neurologic injury, defined as an ICVA or HCVA with MRS &gt; 0 at 24-weeks post-stroke, or a TIA, or a spinal cord infarction.</measure>
    <time_frame>12 month</time_frame>
  </primary_outcome>
  <secondary_outcome>
    <measure>Stroke-free success</measure>
    <time_frame>12 month</time_frame>
    <description>There are two secondary endpoints: 1. first secondary endpoint is the reduction in stroke/TIA incidence at 12 months on the originally implanted HVAD compared to 17.7% (the lower bound of a pre-defined margin of superiority) in a new cohort of subjects receiving optimal blood pressure management; 2. the second secondary endpoint is a non-inferiority test comparing HVAD to control LVAD considering stroke-free success (Modified Rankin Score &lt;4 at 24-weeks post-stroke) at 12 months .</description>
  </secondary_outcome>
